title.narrative: Output 1.2 Social sector ministries and parliament have improved capacity to manage and oversight public finance for children

description.narrative: For the first time ever, the country has conducted a national Multidimensional Poverty measurement, which will shed light on non-monetary dimensions of poverty, inform policies and assess their effectiveness over time. UNICEF also generated new evidence on possible options for child benefits, which could result in increased coverage of young children. The Government and Parliament now have all required information to make an informed decision on this issue and support the government's agenda to invest in human capital as per the National Development Strategy 2018-2040. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/12/2019
